# `.envrc` example (direnv)

Copy the following into **repo root** as `.envrc`, fill in values, then run:

```bash
direnv allow
```

Then you can run `flutter run` without typing `--dart-define` flags manually.

```sh
# Local direnv config (copy to repo root as `.envrc`)
# `.envrc` is gitignored; never commit real secrets.

export HUGGINGFACE_API_KEY="YOUR_HUGGINGFACE_TOKEN"
# Optional: if you want Supabase to initialize from local injection.
# Note: when validating the Firebase Remote Config Supabase flow, keep these
# unset so you can prove the app is sourcing config from Remote Config.
# export SUPABASE_URL="https://YOUR_PROJECT.supabase.co"
# export SUPABASE_ANON_KEY="YOUR_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY"

# Optional
# export GEMINI_API_KEY="..."
# export GOOGLE_MAPS_API_KEY="..."
# export GOOGLE_MAPS_ANDROID_API_KEY="..."

# Optional: Render FastAPI chat demo (see docs/integrations/render_fastapi_chat_demo.md).
# `tool/flutter_dart_defines_from_env.sh` maps these to --dart-define for the direnv flutter wrapper.
# export CHAT_RENDER_DEMO_ENABLED="true"
# export CHAT_RENDER_DEMO_BASE_URL="https://your-service.onrender.com"
# export CHAT_RENDER_DEMO_STRICT="false"
# export CHAT_RENDER_DEMO_SECRET="..."  # only if the FastAPI service uses DEMO_SHARED_SECRET
# export CHAT_RENDER_HF_READ_TOKEN_CALLABLE="issueRenderChatDemoHfReadToken"
# export CHAT_RENDER_HF_READ_TOKEN_CALLABLE_REGION="us-central1"  # omit to use default

# Optional: Firebase Functions emulator — Callable `issueRenderChatDemoHfReadToken` reads this
# when FUNCTIONS_EMULATOR=true (not a Flutter dart-define; export for the shell that runs `firebase emulators:start`).
# export RENDER_CHAT_DEMO_HF_READ_TOKEN="hf_..."

# Optional: make `flutter run` auto-append --dart-define from env (zsh/bash).
# The wrapper injects defines after the subcommand (e.g. `flutter run --dart-define=...`).
export PATH="$(pwd)/tool/direnv/bin:${PATH}"
```
